  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [ ] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (9d64f1f 2022-10-26T00:08:20.899561012Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen one hasn't used a script with a `--broadcast` flag before and submits a script without it, but with `--verify`, the error message is:\r\n```\r\n/path/to/project/broadcast/ScriptName.s.sol/1/dry-run/run-latest.json\": No such file or directory (os error 2)\r\n```\r\nWhile the error should be more helpful, such as \"Cannot verify contracts: flag `--verify` is set, but `--broadcast` isn't and no past deployment was found.\". The current error makes it look like it's a foundry error.",
